Document: Parallax2D
Path: godot/classes/class_parallax2d.rst
Summary: Defines a 2D parallax scrolling effect for child nodes.

Parallax2D is a Node that allows you to create a 2D parallax scrolling effect. This effect is commonly used in 2D games to simulate depth by making background layers move slower than foreground layers.

Inherits: Node2D < CanvasItem < Node < Object

Properties:
scroll_offset (Vector2): The current scroll offset of the parallax layer.
scroll_scale (Vector2): The scale factor for the parallax scrolling. A scale of (0, 0) means the layer won't move at all, while a scale of (1, 1) means it will move at the same speed as the camera.
scroll_speed_scale (Vector2): The speed scale factor for the parallax scrolling. This property is deprecated and will be removed in a future version. Use scroll_scale instead.

Methods:
_process(delta): Called every frame. _process is a virtual method that can be overridden to add custom logic.

The Parallax2D node itself does not render anything. It acts as a container for ParallaxLayer nodes, which define the actual scrolling behavior of the background elements. When the Parallax2D node's scroll offset changes (e.g., due to camera movement), it propagates this change to its child ParallaxLayer nodes, applying their respective scroll scales. This allows for complex parallax effects where different layers move at different speeds relative to the camera.
